                    <msContents>
                        <summary><persName role="aut">Basāwan La‘l bin Nansuk’h Rāy Kāyat’h Saksēnah
                                Bilgrāmī</persName>, pen named <q xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"><addName
                                    type="penname">S̲h̲ādān</addName></q> first composed the
                                <title>Amīr'nāmah</title> (Book of the Prince), a biography of his
                            patron, the first Nawāb of Tonk,<persName role="subject spn"
                                ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/63663612/" key="person_63663612">Amīr
                                Khān (b. 1768, r. 1806–1834)</persName>, in <date
                                calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1824" to="1825">1240 AH (1824–1825
                                CE)</date>. In his preface, he describes how he had then served the
                            Nawāb for twelve years as <hi rend="italic">Nā'ib Munshī</hi> (Associate
                            Secterary). This manuscript, completed by <q xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                >Nā’ib Amīr Munshī</q> for the Nawāb of Tonk's son and successor
                                <persName role="pat">Muḥamamd Wazīr Khān (b. 1807, r.
                                1834–1864)</persName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                when="1860-11-26">12 Jumādà I 1277 (26 Nov 1860)</date> suggests
                            that the author copied this manuscript himself much again later in life,
                            when he had served for some forty-eight years, hence it may be a later
                            revised and extended redaction.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Gaster_MS_Misc_1501-item1">
                            <author role="aut scr" key="person_f8409">
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8409"
                                    >Bilgrām,, Basāwan La‘l bin Nansukh Rāy Kāyath Sakkīnah, fl. ca.
                                    1810–1860</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName type="penname" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Shādān</persName>
                                <persName type="title" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Nā’ib Amīr
                                    Munshī</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="fa"> بساون لعل بلگرامی
                                </persName>؛ <lb/>
                                <persName type="penname" xml:lang="fa">شادان</persName>؛ <lb/>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="fa"/>
                            </author>
                            <editor role="subject" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/63663612"
                                key="person_63663612">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Amīr K̲h̲ān̲,
                                    Nawab of Tonk, b. 1768, r. 1806–1834</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">امیر خان، نواب ٹونک</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <editor role="pat" key="person_f8410">
                                <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Muḥammad Wazīr
                                    K̲h̲ān̲, Nawab of Tonk, b. 1807, r. 1834–1864</persName>; <lb/>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa"> محمد وزیر خان، نواب ٹونک</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_10327">Amīr'nāmah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_10327">امیرنامه</title>

                            <incipit type="basmala" xml:lang="fa"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ
                                    (folio 1b):</locus> بنام شهدار کون و مکان * که فتح و شکست است در
                                حکم آن</incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="257a" to="257a"> برگ ۲۵۷ر (folio
                                    257a):</locus> ز باغ‌ امیدش خزان باد دور * بود دائم او را بـهار
                                سـرور</explicit>
                            <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="257a" to="257a"> برگ ۲۵۷ر (folio
                                    257a):</locus> تمت تمام شد نسخه متبرکه امیر نامه من تصنیف نائب
                                امیر منشی بساون لعل محرره بتاریخ دواز[د]هم ماه جمادی الاولی سنه ۱۱۷۷
                                هجری قمری در عبد نواب معلی القاب گردون وقار نواب محمد وزیر خان نصر
                                جنگ بهادر دام افباله و صاحبقرانی زیور(؟) اختتام پذیرفت.<lb/> نوشته
                                بماند سیه بر سفید * نویسنده را نیست فردا امید. </colophon>
                            <colophon>Completed by <q><persName type="title" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"
                                        >Nā’ib Amīr Munshī</persName></q> for <persName
                                    xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Muḥammad Wazīr
                                    K̲h̲ān̲</persName> on <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                    when="1860-11-26">12 Jumādà I 1277 (26 Nov
                                1860)</date>.</colophon>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>

                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="chart">
                                <support>Textblock of cross-grained, externally sized and polished,
                                    straw-coloured <material>paper</material> possibly handmade in
                                    the <placeName cert="high"
                                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7016788"
                                        key="place_7016788">Rajputana (Rajasthan)</placeName> with
                                    ~8 laid lines per cm and no discernible chain lines.</support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure unit="page" quantity="257">257 folios, 5 flyleaves
                                        endleaves (ff. ii + 257 + iii)</measure>
                                    <!-- CHECK foliation and measure <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
